act terminated) ''as of November 2019''\n* {{flagicon|POL}} Patrycja Swierzewska (LB) (contract terminated) ''as of November 2019''\n{{col-end}}\n\n===Technical staff===\n* '''Head coach:''' Alte Oliver Johansen\n* '''Assistant coach:''' Frode Bjerkan\n* '''Physiotherapists:''' Gaute Alstad Sunde, \u00d8yvind Skarsaune\n* '''Team doctor:''' Nils Ivar Leraand\n\n===Notable former club and National Team players===\n{{col-begin}}\n{{col-2}}\n* {{flagicon|NOR}} [[Annette Skottvoll]]\n* {{flagicon|NOR}} [[Karin Pettersen]]\n* {{flagicon|NOR}} [[Mona Dahle]]\n* {{flagicon|NOR}} [[Ann-Cathrin Eriksen]]\n* {{flagicon|NOR}} [[Trine Haltvik]]\n* {{flagicon|NOR}} [[Kari Solem]]\n* {{flagicon|NOR}} [[Hege Kristine Kvitsand]]\n* {{flagicon|NOR}} [[Vigdis H\u00e5rsaker]]\n* {{flagicon|NOR}} [[Kjersti Beck]]\n* {{flagicon|NOR}} [[Elisabeth Hilmo]]\n* {{flagicon|NOR}} [[Terese Pedersen]]\n* {{flagicon|NOR}} [[Kari Aalvik Grimsb\u00f8]]\n* {{flagicon|NOR}} [[Camilla Herrem]]\n* {{flagicon|NOR}} [[Marit Malm Frafjord]]\n* {{flagicon|NOR}} [[G\u00f8ril Snorroeggen]]\n* {{flagicon|NOR}} [[Pernille Wibe]]\n* {{flagicon|NOR}} [[Mari Molid]]\n* {{flagicon|NOR}} [[Amanda Kurtovic]]\n{{col-2}}\n* {{flagicon|NOR}} [[Maja Jakobsen]]\n* {{flagicon|NOR}} [[Tonje N\u00f8stvold]]\n* {{flagicon|NOR}} [[Marta Tomac]]\n* {{flagicon|NOR}} [[Emilie Hegh Arntzen]]\n* {{flagicon|NOR}} [[Marit R\u00f8sberg Jacobsen]]\n* {{flagicon|NOR}} [[Silje Waade]]\n* {{flagicon|NOR}} [[Tonje Haug Lerstad]]\n* {{flagicon|BRA}} [[Barbara Arenhart]]\n* {{flagicon|CRO}} Suzana Zuljani\n* {{flagicon|CZE}} Iva Zamorska\n* {{flagicon|HUN}} [[Rita Lakatos]]\n* {{flagicon|ISL}} [[Helena \u00d6rvarsd\u00f3ttir]]\n* {{flagicon|SWE}} [[Mia Hermansson-H\u00f6gdahl]]\n* {{flagicon|TUN}} [[Raja Toumi]]\n* {{flagicon|TUR}} [[Yeliz \u00d6zel]]\n{{col-end}}\n\n===Notable former club players===\n{{col-begin}}\n{{col-2}}\n* {{flagicon|NOR}} Kate Mogseth\n* {{flagicon|NOR}} Camilla Solberg\n* {{flagicon|NOR}} Beate Jonassen Grua\n* {{flagicon|NOR}} Ingrid Nyg\u00e5rd Pedersen\n* {{flagicon|NOR}} Sissel Nyg\u00e5rd Pedersen\n* {{flagicon|NOR}} Marthe Florholmen\n* {{flagicon|NOR}} Hilde Stavran Magnussen\n* {{flagicon|NOR}} Maren Villab\u00f8\n* {{flagicon|NOR}} Therese Henden\n* {{flagicon|NOR}} Marte Snorroeggen\n* {{flagicon|NOR}} Nina Stokland\n* {{flagicon|NOR}} Kathrine Hjelmeland\n* {{flagicon|NOR}} Gina Lorentsen\n* {{flagicon|NOR}} Trine Kambu\u00e5s\n* {{flagicon|NOR}} Guro Rundbr\u00e5ten\n* {{flagicon|NOR}} Hanna Yttereng\n{{col-2}}\n* {{flagicon|NOR}} [[June Anden\u00e6s]]\n* {{flagicon|NOR}} [[Inga Berit Svestad]]\n* {{flagicon|NOR}} Maren Gundersen\n* {{flagicon|NOR}} [[Marie Henriksen]]\n* {{flagicon|NOR}} [[Maria Hjertner]]\n* {{flagicon|NOR}} [[Moa H\u00f6gdahl]]\n* {{flagicon|NOR}} [[Kristin Venn]]\n{{col-end}}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{official website|http://www.byaasen.no/}}\n\n{{GRUNDIGligaen}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Byaasen HE}}\n[[Category:Norwegian handball clubs]]\n[[Category:Sport in Trondheim]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox handball club\n| clubname    = By\u00e5sen H\u00e5ndball Elite\n| fullname    = By\u00e5sen H\u00e5ndball Elite\n| short name  = By\u00e5sen HE\n| image       = Byasen.svg\n| founded     = 1921\n| ground      = [[Trondheim Spektrum]], [[Trondheim]]\n| capacity    = 8,600 (since 2019)\n| chairman    = Oddvar Aardahl\n| coach       = Roger Kvannli\n| league      = [[Eliteserien (women's handball)|Eliteserien]]\n| season      = 2018\u201319\n| position    = 6th\n| website     = http://byaasen.no/\n| colour1     = red\n| colour2     = white\n| pattern_la1 = | pattern_b1 =  | pattern_ra1 = | leftarm1 = EF2B2D | body1 = EF2B2D | rightarm1 = EF2B2D | shorts1 = 2B345B | socks1 = FFFFFF\n<!-- Away colours -->\n| pattern_la2 = | pattern_b2 = | pattern_ra2 = | leftarm2 = FFFFFF | body2 = FFFFFF | rightarm2 = FFFFFF | shorts2 = 2B345B | socks2 = FFFFFF\n}}\n'''By\u00e5sen H\u00e5ndball Elite''' is the women's [[handball]] team of the Norwegian multi-sports club [[By\u00e5sen IL]] based in [[Trondheim]]. The team plays in [[Eliteserien (women's handball)|Eliteserien]], the top division in the country, since its promotion in 1982.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://byaasen.no/artikkel/11352|title=By\u00e5sens Historie|trans-title=History of By\u00e5sen|publisher=By\u00e5sen HE official website|date=June 2010|accessdate=2 October 2011|language=Norwegian|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110531000051/http://byaasen.no/artikkel/11352#|archive-date=2011-05-31|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\nThe team's first success came as a third division club, when in 1980 it won the silver medal in the national cup. Among its successes are four domestic league and four domestic cup titles, and the club also has a good reputation in the continental arena, having reached the latest stage of the European cup competitions, including the EHF Cup Winners' Cup final in 2007.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://byaasen.no/artikkel/134687|title=Meritter|trans-title=Merits|publisher=By\u00e5sen HE official website|date=July 2011|accessdate=2 October 2011|language=Norwegian|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120502124925/http://byaasen.no/artikkel/134687#|archive-date=2012-05-02|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\n==Honours==\n*'''Norwegian Championship''':\n**''Winners'': 1984/1985, 1985/1986, 1987/1988, 1988/1989\n*'''Norwegian Cup''':\n**''Winners'': 1988, 1989, 1991, 2007\n**''Finalist'': 2006, 2008, 2009\n*'''[[EHF Women's Cup Winners' Cup|EHF Cup Winners' Cup]]''':\n**''Finalist'': [[2006\u201307 EHF Women's Cup Winner's Cup|2006/2007]]\n\n==European record ==\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n! Season\n! Competition\n! Round\n! Club\n! 1st leg\n! 2nd leg\n! Aggregate\n|-\n| colspan=\"7\" bgcolor=white|\n|-\n| rowspan=\"6\" | [[2016\u201317 Women's EHF Cup|2016\u201317]]\n| rowspan=\"6\" | [[Women's EHF Cup|EHF Cup]]\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|[[2016\u201317 Women's EHF Cup#Round 1|R1]]\n| {{flagicon|SLO}} [[RK Zagorje]]\n| style=\"text-align:c